verbose_text: Macrophages along with other immune cells express adrenergic receptors that bind NE [XREF_BIBR], and have been shown to produce neurotrophic factors such as NGF [XREF_BIBR] and brain derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF) [XREF_BIBR] in human peripheral blood and the human brain [XREF_BIBR], suggesting another possible mechanism in regulation of axonal plasticity may exist in adipose tissue, whereby immune cells are synaptically wired and release neurotrophic factor to nearby nerves.
